           <p class="answerDisplay_fmt" style="display:none;"> <span class="answerBoxLabel_fmt"> <span class="prompt"> This answer is <span class="answer_text">incorrect</span>. </span> </span> <br />You should try to avoid scratching as much as possible, regardless of the length of your fingernails. Bacteria can spread from your skin or from under your nails (even short nails) and infect the rash. Scratching also can lead to increased scarring.</p> 
           <p class="answerDisplay_fmt" style="display:none;"> <span class="answerBoxLabel_fmt"> <span class="prompt"> This answer is <span class="answer_text_cor">correct</span>. </span> </span> <br />You should try to avoid scratching as much as possible, regardless of the length of your fingernails. Bacteria can spread from your skin or from under your nails (even short nails) and infect the rash. Scratching also can lead to increased scarring.</p> 
          </div> 
         </div> 
         <span class="answerBoxLabel_fmt"> <p>When my child or I get the rash from chickenpox, I will need a prescription to stop the itching. </p> </span> 
