       <div class="as_title2">
        Where to go from here
       </div> 
       <div class="as_content"> 
        <p> <b>Talk with your doctor</b> </p> 
        <p>Call your doctor right away if you or your child has a severe headache or constant <a href="http://www.webmd.com/digestive-disorders/digestive-diseases-nausea-vomiting" onclick="return sl(this,'','embd-lnk');">vomiting</a>, sensitivity to bright light, unusual sleepiness or confusion, <a href="http://www.webmd.com/lung/breathing-problems-causes-tests-treatments" onclick="return sl(this,'','embd-lnk');">trouble breathing</a>, or coughing that won't go away. Call your doctor if you notice <a href="http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/symptoms-of-a-skin-infection" onclick="return sl(this,'hw','embd-lnk');">signs of skin infection</a>, such as a continued high fever, increasingly reddening or swollen skin, bigger open sores, or unusual discharge or smell from chickenpox sores. </p> 
        <p>If you are older than age 12 and have not had chickenpox or the chickenpox vaccine, call your doctor if you have been in contact with someone who has chickenpox. This is especially important for <a href="http://www.webmd.com/baby/default.htm" onclick="return sl(this,'','embd-lnk');">pregnant</a> women and for people with <a href="http://www.webmd.com/hw-popup/impaired-immune-system" onclick="return sl(this,'hw','embd-lnk');">impaired immune systems</a>, no matter what age they are.</p> 
        <p class="NoWebPrint">Return to <a href="http://www.webmd.com/children/how-to-control-itching-from-the-chickenpox-rash" onclick="return sl(this,'','embd-lnk');"><img border="0" src="http://img.webmd.com/dtmcms/live/webmd/consumer_assets/site_images/media/interface/actionset.gif" alt="actionset.gif" align="" style="" /></a> <a href="http://www.webmd.com/children/how-to-control-itching-from-the-chickenpox-rash" onclick="return sl(this,'','embd-lnk');">Chickenpox: Controlling the Itch</a></p> 
